==English==

{{wikipedia}}
===Alternative forms===
:'''pu.''' or '''purp.''' in [[heraldic]] contexts.
===Etymology===
From [[Old French]] ''[[purpure]]'' "purple".

===Pronunciation===
*{{IPA|/ˈpəpjuːə/}}
*{{IPA|/ˈpɚpjuɹ/}}

===Noun===
'''purpure'''

#{{tincture}}: A [[purple]] colour on a [[coat of arms]], represented in engraving by [[diagonal]] parallel lines 45 degrees [[clockwise]].
#:* '''1997''': Many authorities reject the authenticity of '''purpure''' as a tincture. &mdash; Brault, ''Early Blazon''

